From: Joe Yen <jyen.tech@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-06-09
Subject: [PATCH 11/10] agentns: create-and-enter via prctl(PR_SET_AGENT_NS)

The legacy clone-flag creation path is dead: the 32-bit clone/unshare flag
space is exhausted, so unshare(2) cannot ever reach a CLONE_NEWAGENT bit
(0x100 aliases CLONE_VM; the replacement 0x400000000ULL is clone3-only).
assay-agentns proves this on the booted kernel: unshare(CLONE_NEWAGENT)
returns EINVAL and /proc/self/agent_session is all zeros.

Route agent-namespace creation through a dedicated prctl op instead:

  - PR_SET_AGENT_NS (PR_AGENT_BASE + 7): create a fresh agent_ns (fresh
    128-bit session id, zeroed counters, cleared intent tag) and install it
    on the calling task's nsproxy. Reachable from plain userspace; no clone
    flag involved.

  - agent_ns_reproxy_current() (kernel/nsproxy.c): builds a new nsproxy via
    the existing static create_new_namespaces(CLONE_NEWAGENT, ...) — which
    takes a reference to every inherited namespace and forks only the
    agent_ns (copy_agent_ns enforces CAP_SYS_ADMIN) — then attaches it with
    switch_task_namespaces(). Lives in nsproxy.c because it needs the static
    nsproxy allocator.

ns_common identity now uses AGENT_NS_TYPE (== the clone3-only flag value)
rather than the old 0x100 alias.

The canonical applier is scripts/apply-agentns.py (idempotent anchor-based
inline edits); this .patch is the human-readable description of the same
change. apply-agentns.py --check fails if a stale 0x100 CLONE_NEWAGENT
creation #define reappears.

Signed-off-by: Joe Yen <jyen.tech@gmail.com>
---
 include/uapi/linux/agent_namespaces.h |  1 +
 kernel/agent_namespaces.c             | 11 +++++++++++
 kernel/nsproxy.c                      | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 28 insertions(+)

--- a/include/uapi/linux/agent_namespaces.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/agent_namespaces.h
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@
 #define PR_GET_AGENT_COUNTERS		(PR_AGENT_BASE + 5)
 #define PR_GET_AGENT_PARENT_ID		(PR_AGENT_BASE + 6)
+#define PR_SET_AGENT_NS			(PR_AGENT_BASE + 7)

--- a/kernel/agent_namespaces.c
+++ b/kernel/agent_namespaces.c
@@ -448,6 +448,17 @@ long agent_ns_prctl(struct task_struct *me, int option,
 	switch (option) {
+	case PR_SET_AGENT_NS:
+		/*
+		 * Create-and-enter a fresh agent namespace for the calling
+		 * task. Unshare-equivalent; no clone flag involved.
+		 */
+		return agent_ns_reproxy_current();
 	case PR_GET_AGENT_SESSION_ID: {

--- a/kernel/nsproxy.c
+++ b/kernel/nsproxy.c
@@ -257,6 +257,22 @@ int unshare_nsproxy_namespaces(unsigned long unshare_flags,
+#ifdef CONFIG_AGENT_NS
+int agent_ns_reproxy_current(void)
+{
+	struct task_struct *tsk = current;
+	struct nsproxy *new_nsp;
+
+	new_nsp = create_new_namespaces(CLONE_NEWAGENT, tsk,
+					current_user_ns(), tsk->fs);
+	if (IS_ERR(new_nsp))
+		return PTR_ERR(new_nsp);
+
+	switch_task_namespaces(tsk, new_nsp);
+	return 0;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(agent_ns_reproxy_current);
+#endif
+
 void exit_nsproxy_namespaces(struct task_struct *p)
